abstract: The president’s tweets, Bill Barr’s doings and the contest for the Democratic nomination made for quite a week of political theater.
snippet: The president’s tweets, Bill Barr’s doings and the contest for the Democratic nomination made for quite a week of political theater.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Katie Barr the door, Gail! That was quite a public rebuke of Donald Trump from Attorney General Bill Barr, who said the president’s incessant tweeting was making his job “impossible.”

abstract: When Kristin and Thomas Schmitt took out a mortgage and bought a house last summer, the German couple's dream looked as if it was coming true. Two months later, they learned that the tire factory where both work would be shut down early next year.
snippet: When Kristin and Thomas Schmitt took out a mortgage and bought a house last summer, the German couple's dream looked as if it was coming true. Two months later, they learned that the tire factory where both work would be shut down early next year.
lead_paragraph: BAMBERG, Germany — When Kristin and Thomas Schmitt took out a mortgage and bought a house last summer, the German couple's dream looked as if it was coming true. Two months later, they learned that the tire factory where both work would be shut down early next year.

abstract: Stocks are opening lower on Wall Street after Apple said it would fail to meet its revenue forecast for the current quarter due to the impact of the virus outbreak in China. Markets fell in Europe and Asia, with the exception of China, which was flat. The S&P 500 fell 0.3% to 3,371 and the Dow Jones Industrial Average dropped 104 points, or 0.4%, to 29,293. The Nasdaq slipped 0.4% to 9,696. Tech stocks saw the biggest early declines, led by Apple and chipmakers. Energy stocks fell along with the price of oil. Bond prices rose and yields declined.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Stocks are opening lower on Wall Street after Apple said it would fail to meet its revenue forecast for the current quarter due to the impact of the virus outbreak in China. Markets fell in Europe and Asia, with the exception of China, which was flat. The S&P 500 fell 0.3% to 3,371 and the Dow Jones Industrial Average dropped 104 points, or 0.4%, to 29,293. The Nasdaq slipped 0.4% to 9,696. Tech stocks saw the biggest early declines, led by Apple and chipmakers. Energy stocks fell along with the price of oil. Bond prices rose and yields declined.
headline_main: Stocks Open Lower on Apple Warning, Virus Outbreak Fears
headline_print_headline: Stocks Open Lower on Apple Warning, Virus Outbreak Fears

abstract: John Bolton, the former national security adviser to President Donald Trump, raised concern on Monday about his unpublished book being "suppressed" by the White House and suggested he should be able to respond to the president's tweets about him.
snippet: John Bolton, the former national security adviser to President Donald Trump, raised concern on Monday about his unpublished book being "suppressed" by the White House and suggested he should be able to respond to the president's tweets about him.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — John Bolton, the former national security adviser to President Donald Trump, raised concern on Monday about his unpublished book being "suppressed" by the White House and suggested he should be able to respond to the president's tweets about him.
headline_main: Bolton Says He Hopes Book Is Not 'Suppressed' by White House

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg’s campaign mounted a direct offensive against a Democratic opponent for the first time, as Bernie Sanders shot back by accusing the billionaire of trying to buy the presidency.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg’s campaign mounted a direct offensive against a Democratic opponent for the first time, as Bernie Sanders shot back by accusing the billionaire of trying to buy the presidency.
lead_paragraph: RENO, Nev. — Former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg’s presidential campaign, which has largely focused its attacks on President Trump, on Monday mounted a frontal offensive against one of his Democratic rivals for the first time, comparing Senator Bernie Sanders’s campaign tactics with those employed by the president.

abstract: In his first public appearance since the impeachment trial, the president’s former national security adviser said he was fighting efforts to suppress his unpublished book.
snippet: In his first public appearance since the impeachment trial, the president’s former national security adviser said he was fighting efforts to suppress his unpublished book.
lead_paragraph: DURHAM, N.C. — John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser to President Trump, suggested on Monday that his unpublished book contained far more revelations than just the campaign to pressure Ukraine for help with domestic politics but said he was fighting “censorship” by the White House.

abstract: Joe Biden’s first two finishes sent his national poll numbers plummeting and put his donors on edge. He wants Nevada to begin his comeback, not accelerate his plunge.
snippet: Joe Biden’s first two finishes sent his national poll numbers plummeting and put his donors on edge. He wants Nevada to begin his comeback, not accelerate his plunge.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — On Friday afternoon, Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s campaign manager, Greg Schultz, convened a conference call with supporters to outline a path forward following two bruising losses in Iowa and New Hampshire.
